{#
retry_stub_files.jinja2 — Stub Retry Prompt Template
SPDX-License-Identifier: Proprietary
Copyright (c) 2025 Novatrax Labs

Renders a structured LLM retry prompt that requests complete implementations
for all remaining stub files.  Groups files by module category with per-category
technology guidance and provides a cross-file importer dependency map so the
LLM can resolve signature requirements from importing modules.

Template Variables:
- retry_hint: Pre-rendered stub listing hint string (from stub_retry_hint.jinja2)
- stub_groups: Dict mapping category name → list of file paths in that category
- importers_map: Dict mapping stub path → list of files that import from it
#}
{{ retry_hint }}

Return ONLY a JSON object whose keys are the file paths listed above and whose values are
the complete, production-ready file contents. Do NOT include any explanatory text outside
the JSON object.

File-type-specific requirements:
{% for category, files in stub_groups.items() %}
=== {{ category | upper }} FILES ===
{% if category == "model" %}
Use SQLAlchemy 2.x: DeclarativeBase, Mapped[T], mapped_column(). Include id, created_at, updated_at.
{% elif category == "schema" %}
Use Pydantic v2: BaseModel, Field(...) with validation constraints, ConfigDict(from_attributes=True).
{% elif category == "service" %}
Use async SQLAlchemy sessions: await session.execute(select(...)), .scalars().all(), session.commit().
{% elif category == "router" %}
Use FastAPI: APIRouter(), typed path/query params, Depends() for DB/auth, proper HTTP status codes.
{% elif category == "auth" %}
Use JWT (python-jose or PyJWT): encode/decode tokens, passlib for password hashing, OAuth2PasswordBearer.
{% elif category == "config" %}
Use pydantic-settings BaseSettings with Field() for env-var loading and validation.
{% else %}
Provide complete, functional implementations — no pass, no return None, no TODO/FIXME.
{% endif %}
Files: {{ files | join(", ") }}

{% endfor %}
Cross-file context (what imports from each stub):
{% for path, importers in importers_map.items() %}
  - {{ path }} is imported by: {{ importers | join(", ") }}
{% endfor %}
